nder rapid social changes. The book will contribute to the current ethnographical research in Vietnam and Southeast Asia and also be of particular interest to those working on society and culture in the geographical region from broader disciplines. It will also appeal to readers who are interested in such topics as late socialism, social transformation, and rural development.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aFamilieszMekong River Delta (Vietnam and Cambodia) 0aFamilies. 0aFamilies; Mekong River Delta (Vietnam and Cambodia). 0aSocial changezMekong River Delta (Vietnam and Cambodia) 0aSocial change. 0aSocial change; Mekong River Delta (Vietnam and Cambodia). 0aVietnamesezMekong River Delta (Vietnam and Cambodia) 0aVietnamese. 0aVietnamese; Mekong River Delta (Vietnam and Cambodia). 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / Rural.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066300608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS eBook Package 2015-2017z978311060667640uhttps://doi.org/10.1355/978981462027740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789814620277423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789814620277.jpg  a978-3-11-060667-6  ISEAS eBook Package 2015-2017c2015d2017  a978-3-11-066300-6  ISEAS Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK